(firstQuint)Single Infusion of Liposomal Amphotericin B in Indian Visceral Leishmaniasis.

 The purpose of this trial is to evaluate the efficacy of single dose amphotericin B in the treatment of VL in India.

 Primary objective: Comparison of the efficacy of single dose of 10 mg/kg of liposomal amphotericin B to amphotericin B deoxycholate with regards to final cure rates Secondary objective:.

 Comparison of the safety of single dose of 10 mg/kg of liposomal amphotericin B to amphotericin B deoxycholate when administered in the proposed dosage regimens.

